:preface 
:p.SLSS is designed to utilize the services provided by Interactive
System Productivity Facility (ISPF).  ISPF is a program product
of IBM.
:p.SLSS Version 4.0.0 is designed to utilize ISPF Version 2.
Dialog Manager commands that are available to ISPF Version 2, such
as 'TBSORT' are used within this version.  Earlier versions of ISPF
are unable to execute this version of SLSS.
SLSS  Version 3.1.0 or earlier will run with eariler releases of ISPF.
:p.This version of SLSS has been tested using ISPF V2.2.0 and TSO/E
1.2.1 and has not been tested under earlier releases of ISPF or TSO.
.sp 2
.ce Version 4.0.0 of SLSS/ISPF Modifications/Enhancements:
.sp
:p.Version 4.0.0 of SLSS/ISPF has the following deletions:
:ul
:li.Administrative Functions has been removed from the primary option
panel and is no longer supported.
:eul
.sp
:p.Version 4.0.0 of SLSS/ISPF has the following enhancements:
:i1.scan 
:i1.edit 
:i1.browse
:i1.keywords
:i1.generic
.sp
:ul
:li.Generic USER ID definition for Browse and Edit authorization.
.sp
:li.Enhanced color support in error, warning and processing panels
and messages.
.sp
:li.Upper and lower case characters allowed in the Manual Title
and Keywords fields.
.sp
:li.Update, add or deletion of keywords as manuals are modified,
added or deleted.
.sp
:li.Maintain the sequence of the library as manuals are added
or deleted.
.sp
:li.Complete manual title is displayed on the Browse manual
selection panel.
.sp
:li.Scrollable list of values (glossary) that may be used as
search values in Option S (SCAN).
.sp
:li.Addition of a field (KEYWORDS) to provide additional
search values words for Options S (SCAN).
.sp
:li.Addition of a field (PROGRAM NO) to provide program number(s)
related to each manual.
.sp
:li.Modifiable variable (TECHCONT) to supply a department or individual
name to be used when error messages are displayed and the user is
informed to contact someone for further information.
:eul
.sp
:body
.ll 76
.* -------------------------------------------------------------- *.
:h1.Introduction
.sp 3
:p.The System Library Subscription Service (SLSS)
is an interactive dialog application that you can use to
aid in creating and maintaining a library.  SLSS may be used
to support an individual library or several libraries which can
be accessed by single or multiple users.
.sp
:p.The term library is used to define a collection of manuals.
The library will contain for each manual, ID, title, order
status, location (were filed), updates, program number(s), keyswords
and audit information.
:h3.Major Functions
.sp
:i1.browse
:i1.edit 
:i1.scan 
:i1.sort 
:i1.print
:i1.delete
:i1.create
:i1.reset
:i1.utility
:i1.authorize
:p.SLSS is an ISPF dialog that you use at a display terminal.
The functions available to you include:
.sp 2
:ul.
:li.BROWSE existing libraries.
:li.EDIT existing libraries.
:li.CREATE new libraries.
:li.DELETE entire library or selected entries within a library.
:li.PRINT listing of manuals in the library or manuals on order.
:li.SORT library either in Manual ID, location or title sequence.
:li.AUTHORIZE users to browse and/or edit library.
:li.UTILITY to maintain library owner and location.
:li.RESET library and related files if abnormal termination of the
dialog session occurs.
:li.SCANNING of library by any word contained in the title or
any additional keywords defined.
:li.SCROLLING of data within library within while using the
edit or browse functions.
:li.SPLIT SCREEN capability that allows you to partition the
display screen.  Duplicate session of SLSS are not recommended.
:li.DEBUG capability that allows you to trace the session while in
use.
:eul
:h3.SLSS Hierarchy
.sp
:i1.browse
:i1.edit 
:i1.create
:i1.library administrator
:i1.owner
:p.Internal to SLSS is a hierarchy that controls authority
and access to libraries.  There are four levels of access
within SLSS.
The highest level is assigned to a single user known as the
Library Administrator.  Assigning the administrator is done at
intialization time of SLSS (refer to Intialization for further
information).  The Administrator has the authority to select
any option within SLSS for any library within SLSS.
:p.The second level within SLSS is the Library
Owner.  The owner is assigned at the time the library is created
and can be modified or re-assigned by the owner of library.
:p.The third level is the authority to edit an individual library.
This authority is assigned or modified by the owner of the library.
:p.The fourth level is the
browse authority, and is also assigned or modified by the owner of
the library.
.sp 2
.*
.*
.*
