.sp
:h3.Split Screen
.sp
:p.Split screen mode allows you the partition the display screen into
two logical screens.  The top and bottom screens are treated as
though they were displayed on independent terminals.  This
facility is available during a SLSS session.
.sp
:h3.SLSS Termination
.sp
:i1.browse
:i1.sort 
:p.To terminate SLSS, you select option X from the primary selection
menu or press the END key.
When this done the master control file is
updated to reflect any changes to a specific library.
.*
.*===============================================================
.*  chapter break                                               *
.*===============================================================
.*
:h1.BROWSE (OPTION 1)
.sp 2
:i1.browse
:p.The browse option allows you to display information for each
manual stored in the selected library.
When you select browse, a panel is displayed to allow
you to scroll to locate a desired manual.  Once located the
manual can be selected to view additional detail.  To select a
manual enter a 'S' to the left of the Manual ID and press the
enter key.
All three lines of the manual Title are displayed.
.sp
:i1.browse
:i1.edit 
:i1.sort 
:p.In the upper-right hand side of the panel on the third
line will be displayed the library
that is currently being browsed and the sort sequence of the
library. 
.*
.*
.*
