:h1.EDIT (OPTION 2)
.sp 3
:i1.edit 
:i1.create
:i1.delete
:p.The edit option allows you create, modify or delete manuals
in the selected library.
When the edit option is selected a panel is displayed to allow
you to scroll to locate a desired manual.  Once located the
manual can be selected to edit additional detail.  To select a
manual enter a 'S' to the left of the Manual ID and press the
enter key.
.sp
:p.If searching for a specific manual enter the Manual ID
in the option field and press enter.  If the Manual ID is located
an auto scroll will be performed placing the desired Manual ID as the
first selectable manual.  If the Manual ID is not located a panel
will be displayed indicating so.
.sp
:i1.edit 
:i1.delete
:i1.print
:i1.sort 
:p.In the upper-right hand side of the panel on the third
line will be displayed the Library name
that is currently being edited along with the sort sequence
of the library.
.*
.*
.*
