:h1.UTILITY (OPTION 3)
.sp 3
:i1.browse
:i1.edit 
:i1.scan 
:i1.delete
:i1.print
:i1.sort 
:i1.authorize
:i1.utility
:i1.owner
:p.The utility option provides a variety of functions for libraries,
delete entire library, build keyword scan file,
print reports, sort library, authorize browse, authorize edit,
modify library information and recovery after abnormal
termination.
.sp
:i1.keywords
:i1.browse
:i1.edit 
:i1.scan 
:i1.create
:i1.delete
:i1.print
:i1.sort 
:i1.utility
:i1.reset
:i1.owner
:p.The following figure is the utility selection panel.
.*
.*
.*
.bf GT15 
:fig id=opt030  frame=none place=inline
 
 ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
| ------------- SLSS (Utilities) ------------------------------------------------ |
| OPTION ===>                                                                     |
|                                                                                 |
|    Enter option for library: TECH                                               |
|                                                                                 |
|                                                                                 |
|    1  DELETE      - Delete library                                              |
|                                                                                 |
|    2  KEYWORDS    - Create Keyword scan file                                    |
|                                                                                 |
|    3  PRINT       - Produce hardcopy output                                     |
|                                                                                 |
|    4  SORT        - Sort library                                                |
|                                                                                 |
|    5  BROWSE AUTH - Add/Change/Delete users allowed to browse library           |
|                                                                                 |
|    6  EDIT AUTH   - Add/Change/Delete users allowed to edit library             |
|                                                                                 |
|    7  LIBRARY     - Add/Change/Delete library name, owner, location             |
|                                                                                 |
|    8  RESET       - Reset Library and Enqueue after an error has occured        |
|                                                                                 |
|                                                                                 |
|                                                                                 |
 ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 
:figcap.Utility Selection Panel
:efig
.pf
.sp
:i1.delete
:i1.utility
:p.The following describes each of the utility functions.
.*
:h2.DELETE (OPTION 3.1)
.sp 3
:i1.scan 
:i1.delete
:i1.utility
:i1.owner
:p.The owner of the library and the SLSS administrator are the only
users allowed to select this option.
This utility option will delete the entire library and all associated
entries in the control file, keyword scan file if build,
additional location file if built and the enqueue file.
.sp
:i1.delete
:p.Once the option is selected the following panel is displayed.
.*
.*
.*
.bf GT15 
:fig id=opt031  frame=none place=inline
 
 ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
|                                                                                 |
| ------------ SLSS (Delete Library) -------------------------------------------- |
|                                                                                 |
|                                                                                 |
|                                                                                 |
|                                                                                 |
|  Deleting library:  SAMP                                                        |
|                                                                                 |
|  This selected option will delete all table entries for the selected library.   |
|  The library entry will be deleted from the control file and the enqueue file   |
|  will be deleted also.                                                          |
|                                                                                 |
|                 Press ENTER KEY to continue creation process                    |
|                                                                                 |
|                 Press END KEY to terminate process                              |
|                                                                                 |
|                                                                                 |
|                                                                                 |
|                                                                                 |
|                                                                                 |
|                                                                                 |
|                                                                                 |
|                                                                                 |
|                                                                                 |
 ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 
:figcap.Delete Library Panel
:efig
.pf
.sp
:p.The user must confirm delete library request or cancel.
Confirm the request by pressing the enter key.
ancel the request pressing the END PF Key or entering the end
command. 
.sp
:i1.scan 
:i1.delete
:p.If the request is confirmed the user will be supplied the following
panel with the delete status of each file and control entries.
If the delete is successful the return codes will be zero for
each listed entry otherwise a non-zero code will be displayed.
.*
.*
.*
